                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, but careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <date>Second half of the 18th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the donor; name of the king,
                           patriarch and metropolitan; incipit of Text I (fol. 37r); titles, initial
                           lines or initial word of the prayers to be read; directives to the
                           ministers; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals. 
 On the incipit page of Text I (fol. 37r) a few lines are
                           rubricated (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Daily readings are indicated by the names of the
                              days of the week crudely written in the upper margin, in a secondary
                              hand in pencil: ዘቀዳም: <locus target="#16r">fol. 16r</locus>. ዘሐሙስ:
                                 <locus target="#23r">fol. 23r</locus>. ዘአርብ: <locus target="#34v">fol. 34v</locus>. ዘረብዕ: <locus target="#42r">fol.
                              42r</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>- Title ፃሎተ፡ እጣን is written on the front board with red paint. - Spaces for rubrication left unfilled: fols. 54v-55r. - Compressed writing: <locus target="#55v">fol.  55v</locus>. - Pen trials: fols. 43r, 57v. - The name G[äbrä] ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer crudely written in pen: <locus target="#44r">fol.  44r</locus>. - Doodles: fols. 56r-v, 57r-v.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
