               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0115GMG">Gänaḥti Qǝddǝst Māryām / GMG</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1779" notAfter="1796">King Takla Giyorgis (r. 1779-84,
                        1788-89, 1794-95, 1795-96, 1798-99, 1800) is mentioned on <locus target="#13r">13r</locus>, 34r, 34v. Metropolitan Yosab II (in tenure ca.
                        1770-1803) is also mentioned (<locus target="#33v">33v</locus>, 35r) and
                        called ʾIyosab on <locus target="#4r">4r</locus>. Patriarch Yosef (<locus target="#34v">34v</locus>) is most probably John XVIII, Patriarch of
                        Alexandria in 1769-96 whose lay name was Joseph (?).</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>Za-Walda Māryām is mentioned in supplications
                     formulas (4v, 6r, 16v).</provenance></history>
